entities.name: ElizaOS
entities.description: A composable, open-source AI agent framework focused on modularity, maintainability, and developer experience. It supports various AI models and plugins to expand agent capabilities.

entities.name: RAG
entities.description: Retrieval-Augmented Generation, a technique used to enhance the capabilities of language models by integrating external knowledge sources.

entities.name: REST API
entities.description: Representational State Transfer Application Programming Interface, a set of rules and conventions for building and interacting with web services.

entities.name: GitHub
entities.description: A web-based platform and version control system used for software development and collaboration. It hosts Git repositories and provides tools for project management.

entities.name: AWS Bedrock
entities.description: A cloud service that provides access to a range of foundational AI models for building generative AI applications.

entities.name: Google Generative AI
entities.description: A suite of AI models developed by Google, including Gemini, designed for conversational AI, content generation, and other generative tasks.

entities.name: Gemini
entities.description: A family of multimodal large language models developed by Google AI, designed to understand and operate across text, images, audio, video, and code.

entities.name: Ollama
entities.description: An open-source platform that allows users to run large language models locally on their machines, simplifying the deployment and interaction with LLMs.

entities.name: OpenRouter
entities.description: A service that provides a unified API for accessing various large language models from different providers.

entities.name: Bun
entities.description: A fast JavaScript runtime, bundler, test runner, and package manager. Logo is a white bun/dumpling on black.
